\begin_layout Section*
The REPL:
 Your Experimental Sandbox
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sometimes you don't want to write a whole script just to see how a Regex behaves or how a List transforms.
 You want an immediate answer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By running
\emph on
 scala-cli repl .
\emph default
,
 you launch an interactive session that is context-aware.
 It doesn't just give you a blank slate;
 it loads every dependency and every class defined in your current project.
 All in an environment that gives you immediate feedback:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
# Launch the REPL with your project's superpowers from DOS/shell prompt
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
scala-cli repl .
\end_layout

